                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1429" type="surname" value="M'DONALD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1429" type="given" value="ANGUS"></interp>ANGUS M'DONALD</persName>
                  </hi>. I belong to the <hi rend="italic">Dreadnought</hi> Hospital ship. The prisoner slept next to me in my cabin—in the afternoon of the I5th of October I had a purse containing two half-crowns, 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and the French pieces—I put them into my jacket pocket, under my head, when I went to bed—at half-past seven o'clock next morning I missed them—the boat<lb></lb>swain found this money on the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JOHN LORD</hi>. I am boatswain. After this complaint about the money. I spoke to the prisoner—he said the money belonged to him—I found 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., one five-franc piece, two single francs, and some coppers on him—I took him before the captain, and then he said he picked it up under the hammock.</p>
               <p>
